<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>megacarpus</i> is dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Adenostoma</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Adenostoma</i> <i>sparsifolium</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>spinosus</i>, <i>Cercocarpus</i> <i>montanus</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>cinereum</i>, <i>Hesperoyucca</i> <i>whipplei</i>, <i>Heteromeles</i> <i>arbutifolia</i>, <i>Malosma</i> <i>laurina</i>, <i>Quercus</i> <i>berberidifolia</i>, <i>Rhamnus</i> <i>ilicifolia</i> and <i>Salvia</i> <i>mellifera</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Juglans</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Quercus</i> <i>agrifolia</i> or <i>Umbellularia</i> <i>californica</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 4 m; canopy is intermittent to continuous. Herbaceous layer is sparse or occasionally grassy. </div>
</div>

        
