<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Ceanothus megacarpus </i>is an obligate seeder. Heat breaks the dormancy of its refractory seeds, which then germinate following winter rains (Montygierd-Loyba and Keeley 1987). Seedling survivorship is low in the first post-fire year but levels off in subsequent years (Keeley et al. 2006). Dense stands grow quickly. They self-thin soon after fire, and densities decrease in the first 20-30 years of growth (Schlesinger and Gill 1978, Montygierd-Loyba and Keeley 1987). A fire cycle between 25 and 55 or more years should maintain or promote <i>C. megacarpus. </i></div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Medium (25-55 years)
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
